On Tue, 18 Feb 2003, Thomas Boyd wrote:

> I have a stock DP1600 71 bus motor.  That includes the stock
distributor and vac can.  I think I read somewhere that the timing is to
be set at 5 degrees BTDC at idle.
>
> Is this correct?  Any suggestions on timing a 71?

5 degrees after top dead center.  You really should get a Bentley, as the
procedure isn't quite as easy as the earlier buses.

